      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ARTISTRY IN MOTION (1) returns for the Wolfe camp. Was thrown in the deep end last prep on the back of some strong performances when tackling the LR Belgravia Stakes at Ascot. Has his share of ability and has jumped out strongly in readiness. Expecting him to make a bright start to the campaign. PLAYING QUEST (6) is threatening to strike through and gets a great chance on the quick back-up after a good effort on Quokka Day. If Parnham can utilise the inside pillar he will prove tough to stop. ZORBRIST (3) is backing up quickly after finishing a long neck away at Geraldton just eight days ago. Shoulders strong peaks and all three of his wins have come at this distance. Have to take seriously. JAZALOT (4) finished second two runs back at Bunbury then improved last time out to score here. Has been kept fresh for this with 46 days in-between and drops back slightly. Confidence added with Fiore taking over. BANNERED (5) is mixing his form but can threaten if on-song.",
